 Kemi Olaitan in Ibadan Mobile phone manufacturer, Itel has presented a brand new car to a winner of its Big Day scratch and win promo, Oyewole Adeyinka. Adeyinka was rewarded with a brand new Hyundai Sonata car after making a purchase of Itel A58 smartphone in February, keying into the company’s sales promotional offer. The Southwest Zonal Coordinator, National Lottery Regulatory Commission (NLRC), Mr. Tayo Fasuhanmi, while speaking at the presentation, held at Solat Electronics Store, Mokola, Ibadan, enjoined Nigerians to always verify from the commission the authenticity of most promotional sales from corporate organizations to prevent being swindled by suspected fraudster. He explained that the commission was involved in the process of the raffle draw, affirming that the process was fair, transparent and in line with regulatory standard. Fasuhanmi said the Commission was involved from the beginning of the process, stating that the commission is currently handling many cases of customers who have fallen victims of fraudulent promo by some organisations. The Marketing Manager, Itel Nigeria and West Africa (Region 1), Mr. Oke Umurhohwo, in his remarks, said the Itel brand remained customer centric with a regular reward system for customers, adding that it would not relent in providing services and products that would help every Nigerian enjoy better life. While urging Nigerians to take advantage of its new Easter sales promo, Umurhohwo noted that the company enjoys ensuring that customers are satisfied with her products. He said, “We are always after simplifying the lives of our consumers through our products and we derive great joy in knowing that our products make life easier for them. We won’t stop, we won’t relent and we will always make sure to provide services and products that will help each and every Nigerian enjoy better life.”